";i:41;s:86:"This exercise strengthens the dorsiflexors the ankle muscles in the front of your leg.";i:42;s:70:"Stand up tall and use the back of a chair or a countertop for balance.";i:43;s:40:"Keep your feet about hip distance apart.";i:44;s:63:"Slowly lift your toes up while keeping your heels on the floor.";i:45;s:32:"Upper Body Wheelchair Exercises.";i:46;s:66:"This first group of wheelchair exercises works the chest and arms.";i:47;s:60:"Sit up straight in your chair and pull in your belly button.";i:48;s:67:"Doing this engages your abs so they help support your back muscles.";i:49;s:75:"This is the standard starting position for nearly all wheelchair exercises.";i:50;s:94:"Chair Exercises and Lifting Weights 2 For the exercises in this hand out here is a FITT guide.";i:51;s:117:"Frequency 2 to 4 times a week Intensity Weight should feel challenging but not so hard that you compromise your form.";i:52;s:54:"Your muscles should feel tired at the end of each set.";i:53;s:13:"How to do it.";i:54;s:135:"Start on the edge of the chair knees bent and together with feet flat on the floor hands just outside of hips and elbows slightly bent.";i:55;s:143:"Squeeze knees and cheeks together tightly while pushing down with hands extending elbows youll sit taller but you should never leave your seat.";i:56;s:136:"Place the palms of your hands on the chairarms straightand close to your hips and carefully slide your bottom off the edge of the chair.";i:57;s:183:"Keeping your upper arms close to your torso bend them to slower your body downward a couple of inches then press through your palms and straighten your arms to raise yourself back up.";i:58;s:59:"Sit on the edge of your chair with your arms by your sides.";i:59;s:98:"Extend your right leg out straight and flex your foot so that just the right heel is on the floor.";i:60;s:63:"Lift your leg up as high as you can without rounding your back.";i:61;s:68:"Keeping your foot flexed engages the muscles in the shins and ankle.";i:62;s:37:"Hold for three counts and then lower.";i:63;s:303:"The American Council on Exercise named the standard captains chair crunch one of the most effective ab exercises for stimulating the rectus abdominis those six-pack abs muscles and obliques at the sides of your torso after performing a small study that pitted the move against 12 other popular ab moves.";i:64;s:92:"Basic sit to stand exercise 1 min 5 sec in video Scootwalk hips up to the edge of the chair.";i:65;s:33:"Bring toes back underneath knees.";i:66;s:47:"Use arms to push off the chair or off of knees.";i:67;s:91:"Lean forward a little to bring nose over toes and push up with legs to a standing position.";i:68;s:31:"Chair workout for leg strength.";i:69;s:82:"The number of activities reps and sets depending on your fitness level weight etc.";i:70;s:51:"So its hard to suggest a program that fits for all.";i:71;s:96:"The best is if you try these chair exercises so you will know how many reps and sets you can do.";}}